						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Rājarāja I Year 19: 1004 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. Begins with the <hi rend="italic">meykīrtti, Tirumagaḷ pōla.</hi> Seems to record the temple officials, <hi rend="italic">ūrār, nagarattār</hi> and <hi rend="italic">dēvaraḍiyar</hi> collectively called <hi rend="italic">Karmakkiḻavar</hi> had decided not to collect any taxes such as <hi rend="italic">veṭṭi, vēdiṉai amañji</hi> and other taxes from the citizens who settled in the street called Adhi •••• perunteruvu. The citizens were also granted the right to sell or mortgage their houses. Any violation of this arrangement will be met with fines.</p>						

						</summary>
